# Harmonic Set

If $(\bbr, d)$ is a metric set and $E \subset \bbr$, then $$ E = \{ \frac{1}{n}: n = 1, 2, \ldots \} \cup \{ 0 \} $$
is compact.

<div class="proof">

Let $\{ G_\alpha \}_{\alpha \in A}$ be an open cover. Then there exists $\alpha_0$ such that $0 \in G_{\alpha_0}$. So
there also exists an $r > 0$ such that $N_r(0) \subset G_{\alpha_0}$. Choose $m$ such that $\frac{1}{m} < r$, and
$G_{\alpha_1}, \ldots, G_{\alpha_{m-1}}$ such that each $\frac{1}{n} \in G_{\alpha_n}$. Thus 
$G_{\alpha_0}, G_{\alpha_1}, \ldots, G_{\alpha_{m-1}}$ gives a finite cover ($G_{\alpha_0} contains all elements with $n \geq m$
leaving a finite number of sets to manage the remaining elements lying outside).


</div>

